\q1
\v 7 They go from strength to strength.
\q1 Every one of them appears before God in Tsiyyon.
\q1
\v 8 Army commander God Yahweh, hear my prayer.
\q1 God of Yakov, listen to what I’m saying. \qs (Instrumental break.)\qs*
\q1
\v 9 God, watch over our \add defender\add*.
\q1 Show concern for your anointed \add one\add*.
\q1
\v 10 \add Yes,\add* one day in your courtyards is better than a thousand elsewhere.
\q1 I would rather be a doorkeeper in my God’s house,
