\q1
\v 1 Yahweh, you’ve showed favour to your \add country\add*.
\q1 You have restored Yakov’s well-being.
\q1
\v 2 You have forgiven your people’s \add disobedience\add*.
\q1 You’ve covered over all their sin. \qs (Instrumental break.)\qs*
\q1
\v 3 You have withdrawn all your rage.
\q1 You’ve turned back from your hot anger.
\q1
\v 4 Restore us, God \add who saves us\add*,
\q1 and \add don’t stay upset\add* with us.
\q1
\v 5 Will you be angry with us forever?
\q1 Will you remain angry throughout future generations?
\q1
\v 6 Won’t you revive us again,
\q1 then your people could be happy about you.
\q1
\v 7 Show us your loyal commitment, Yahweh.
\q1 Grant us your salvation.
\q1
\v 8 I will listen to what Yahweh God says,
\q1 because he will make peace with his people—his faithful ones,
\q1 yet they mustn’t turn \add back\add* again to \add doing foolish things\add*.
